Amen. The paragraph quoted from patriach.org is tragic. You find similar statements in Philip Lancaster&#039;s Family Man, Family Leader (although there is much good also):

&quot;The family is central to God&#039;s plan to advance the gospel and kingdom of Jesus...&quot;

&quot;The home has always been the foundation and center of true faith in the world...&quot;

&quot;Throughout the ages the family has been the nursery of faith for each new generation, the primary place in which Christian discipleship has occurred...&quot;

Statements such as these give the impression that the church has been replaced by the family. This is what I would describe as the radical aspects of FIC. From this, men such as Scott Brown need to be distinguished.
